1
00:00:09,530 --> 00:00:11,410
♪Way Way to You♪

2
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,400
♪Way Way to You♪

3
00:00:27,050 --> 00:00:30,600
♪On My Way to You♪

4
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:35,080
=Way To You=

5
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:37,070
(Highlights)
Our next mission

6
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:39,150
(Duet performance assessment)
is to teach performance.

7
00:00:39,150 --> 00:00:41,810
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

8
00:00:41,810 --> 00:00:43,150
Two, two, three, four, five.

9
00:00:43,150 --> 00:00:44,170
It may not look great,

10
00:00:44,170 --> 00:00:45,320
but it's the best among it.

11
00:00:46,030 --> 00:00:46,690
I think it looks good.

12
00:00:46,690 --> 00:00:48,730
If we match it with the right costumes
and good makeup,

13
00:00:48,730 --> 00:00:49,360
it should look great.

14
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:51,830
Last night, someone left
without permission.

15
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,340
His class will be suspended today.

16
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:57,140
(What happened exactly?)

17
00:00:57,260 --> 00:00:59,630
(Practiced for 20 minutes last week)
We'll have a dance game now.

18
00:00:59,630 --> 00:01:01,020
(Practiced for 20 minutes last week)
You get 20 minutes practice.

19
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:05,940
(How will their performance look like?)

20
00:01:09,170 --> 00:01:10,650
(Prepare for assessment/duet)
How's the practice coming along?

21
00:01:10,650 --> 00:01:12,460
(Nail first place)
I think we can take first place.

22
00:01:16,460 --> 00:01:17,340
Do you want first place?

23
00:01:17,620 --> 00:01:18,710
(Confident)
We'll definitely get first place.

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,210
I look forward to it.

25
00:01:21,310 --> 00:01:23,230
It's fine. At least being last means
I'm first in the countdown.

26
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:24,970
(A unique mindset)
We're either the best or the worst.

27
00:01:24,970 --> 00:01:25,990
Being in the middle is lame.

28
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:30,310
Are you guys ready?

29
00:01:30,310 --> 00:01:31,480
Yes!

30
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:33,290
Who wants to volunteer?

31
00:01:33,610 --> 00:01:34,490
Volunteer yourself.

32
00:01:34,490 --> 00:01:37,770
(Who will be the first group?)

33
00:01:38,030 --> 00:01:39,100
Let him pick.

34
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:41,050
(Eye contact confirmation)
You want to try?

35
00:01:41,930 --> 00:01:42,580
Okay.

36
00:01:42,580 --> 00:01:43,560
Alright. We'll go first!

37
00:01:43,650 --> 00:01:46,050
(The first group
to volunteer to perform)

38
00:01:51,510 --> 00:01:52,290
Great.

39
00:01:53,470 --> 00:01:55,740
(Duet: Tai & Deaw)

40
00:02:04,220 --> 00:02:05,400
(A small mistake)

41
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,890
(Panicking)

42
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:10,100
(Catching up on rhythm)

43
00:02:13,140 --> 00:02:14,890
(Smooth positioning)

44
00:02:35,650 --> 00:02:36,620
(Thumbs up)

45
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:37,810
That was great!

46
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:41,340
(Comfort partner)
Very good.

47
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,400
Next up is...

48
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,930
(Duet: Eugene & Cannon)

49
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,410
(Cool eye contact)

50
00:02:55,790 --> 00:02:57,650
(Synchronized)

51
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,780
(Excellent chemistry)

52
00:03:07,110 --> 00:03:08,210
Next.

53
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:11,630
Our dance is a little comedic.

54
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:13,330
A bit more humorous.

55
00:03:13,330 --> 00:03:14,290
(Excited)
Comedy?

56
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:18,890
(Leaning forward)

57
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:20,410
(Letting go)

58
00:03:20,420 --> 00:03:22,380
A literal "up and down".

59
00:03:27,070 --> 00:03:28,010
(Wink)

60
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,130
(Ahh my eyes)

61
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:32,620
(Wink again)

62
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:34,640
(Conident)

63
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,180
(Tense body.
The one responsible for dancing)

64
00:03:42,610 --> 00:03:44,770
(Trying not to laugh)

65
00:03:47,110 --> 00:03:47,940
(Looks messy)

66
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:52,730
(Confused)

67
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:56,760
(Most relaxed)

68
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:58,630
Honestly, when you're performing,

69
00:03:58,820 --> 00:04:01,790
I get worried if you're not confident.

70
00:04:02,510 --> 00:04:03,890
So for me,

71
00:04:03,890 --> 00:04:06,290
performance isn't about
whether the dance is good or not.

72
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:09,480
What matters is making
the audience happy.

73
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,600
(Performance should deliver joy)

74
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:16,330
And I felt happy
while watching you guys.

75
00:04:16,330 --> 00:04:18,240
(Tai & Deaw brought joy to viewers)
Thank you.

76
00:04:19,330 --> 00:04:22,870
He's great too,
but he kept looking down and laughing.

77
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:24,920
So be more confident.

78
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:30,060
(Producers preparing to score)

79
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,940
I'm so nervous now.

80
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:36,410
It's okay. Just be the last.

81
00:04:36,410 --> 00:04:37,400
You'll have room for improvement.

82
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,840
(Positive mindset)
What if you get a good place

83
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:39,900
(Positive mindset)
and then drop the next time?

84
00:04:41,530 --> 00:04:42,560
Which place do you want?

85
00:04:42,830 --> 00:04:44,000
Which place?

86
00:04:44,230 --> 00:04:45,630
Honestly, it doesn't matter.

87
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:47,770
I want first place, but...

88
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:50,520
That's normal.
Everyone wants first place.

89
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:52,320
But if you don't, it's actually fine.

90
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,460
(Positive mindset +1)

91
00:04:54,490 --> 00:04:55,550
Any ranking is fine.

92
00:04:55,810 --> 00:04:57,490
Really. We're the best.

93
00:04:57,490 --> 00:04:58,080
Yes.

94
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,330
We're all the best.

95
00:04:59,330 --> 00:05:00,100
Yup.

96
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:02,400
You'll judge the performance.

97
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:02,770
Yes.

98
00:05:02,770 --> 00:05:04,230
I'll judge the dance.

99
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:04,990
Yes.

100
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:05,930
We'll judge separately.

101
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:06,290
Okay.

102
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:08,060
For me,

103
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:10,830
Leo's team gets six points.

104
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:12,030
Jony is five.

105
00:05:12,220 --> 00:05:13,220
Tai is four.

106
00:05:15,490 --> 00:05:16,360
Finish.

107
00:05:16,710 --> 00:05:18,170
Wait a second.

108
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:23,850
So

109
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,240
the first place is...

110
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:29,460
(Which group will win first place?)

111
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:30,440
Done.

112
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,250
Alright, everyone.

113
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,940
We have

114
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:39,030
completed the assessment

115
00:05:39,030 --> 00:05:42,060
and chosen the winners.

116
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,680
How should I put it?

117
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,490
We've ranked first, second,
and third places.

118
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:49,090
(Announcing the top three)

119
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:51,560
Third place is...

120
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:52,410
Nervous.

121
00:05:53,830 --> 00:05:54,650
is...

122
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,890
(Third place: Jony & Leo)
Leo & Jony!

123
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,520
Second place is...

124
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:10,250
Tai & Deaw.

125
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,250
Congratulations.

126
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:22,290
First place...

127
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:29,530
I felt we did well that day.

128
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:31,860
So when the third and second place
was announced,

129
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:33,610
I thought we could be the first.

130
00:06:35,410 --> 00:06:36,670
Tron!

131
00:06:36,670 --> 00:06:37,900
What?

132
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:38,960
(Caught off guard)

133
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:42,030
Congratulations!

134
00:06:42,030 --> 00:06:43,320
Thank you.

135
00:06:44,090 --> 00:06:45,110
Congratulations.

136
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:47,670
Congratulations!

137
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:49,330
I never expected it.

138
00:06:49,330 --> 00:06:51,770
I think Tron and I could get first place

139
00:06:51,770 --> 00:06:54,790
because we did well
with the performance part.

140
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:57,320
So it raised our overall score.

141
00:06:58,150 --> 00:07:00,350
I still feel a little surprised.

142
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:03,680
Deep down, I felt like we should
at least be in the top three.

143
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,950
We'll work harder next time

144
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:06,350
to get first place.

145
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:09,020
(Rankings
First place: Tron & Pippin)

146
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:11,140
(Second place: Tai & Deaw
Third place: Jony & Leo)

147
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:13,260
Now we've announced the winners.

148
00:07:13,260 --> 00:07:15,190
For our next activity,

149
00:07:15,670 --> 00:07:17,440
we've prepared songs for everyone

150
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,910
and show you all a demo.

151
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,960
Then

152
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:25,800
the top three winners just now

153
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:28,850
will get to pick the songs first.

154
00:07:28,850 --> 00:07:30,010
(Top three gets to pick first)

155
00:07:30,010 --> 00:07:30,920
Okay.

156
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,830
Alright, let's see
what songs are available.

157
00:07:35,210 --> 00:07:37,060
(Song reveal)

158
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:40,830
(First song: Hip Hop)

159
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:42,360
That's cool.

160
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:44,560
Do you want this song?

161
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:46,140
It's nice.

162
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:49,380
(Likes it)

163
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:52,120
(Second song: K-pop)
K-pop.

164
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:59,380
(Second song: K-pop)

165
00:08:00,130 --> 00:08:01,940
It's tough.

166
00:08:02,230 --> 00:08:06,830
I think this is better
than the first one.

167
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,390
Kung fu.

168
00:08:09,910 --> 00:08:10,570
I want this one.

169
00:08:10,570 --> 00:08:13,660
(Likes both)
This one? Me too.

170
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:17,100
Oh my god.

171
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:19,230
Oh my goodness.

172
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:21,130
How do you even dance to this?

173
00:08:22,090 --> 00:08:23,700
Can you do this?

174
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:25,860
I can't.

175
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,650
Each option.

176
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:29,330
(Selection begins)
There are four options in total.

177
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:34,010
Each option can only be chosen twice,

178
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,300
and it must be chosen at least once.

179
00:08:39,410 --> 00:08:40,060
Latin?

180
00:08:40,180 --> 00:08:41,470
(Wants to challenge Latin)

181
00:08:41,470 --> 00:08:42,110
Challenge?

182
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,870
Do we want to challenge it?

183
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:45,680
Can we?

184
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,230
Sure. I'm okay.

185
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:48,790
(Agreement reached)
Let's try.

186
00:08:50,410 --> 00:08:51,230
We pick Latin too.

187
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:53,620
(Picked Chinese dance)
Then we'll choose Chinese dance.

188
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:54,980
Do you have any ideas?

189
00:08:58,190 --> 00:08:59,110
I think we should pick the first one.

190
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:00,750
(Pick the first option, Hip-hop)
The first one. Sure.

191
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:05,810
So let's see which ones
you've decided on.

192
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:07,810
Chinese dance.

193
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:09,530
Hip-hop.

194
00:09:11,310 --> 00:09:12,110
Latin.

195
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:15,950
(Song selection results
Chines dance: Tron & Pippin)

196
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:16,890
(Hip-hop: Tai & Deaw
Latin: Jony & Leo)

197
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:21,990
The remaining three groups,
please send a representative

198
00:09:21,990 --> 00:09:23,860
for a game of Rock, Paper, Scissors

199
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:26,350
to decide your song selection order.

200
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:29,010
(U.Jay lost)

201
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:30,490
You're last.

202
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:32,000
Scissor,paper, rock.

203
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,780
(Kai loses once)

204
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,160
Scissor,paper, rock.

205
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:37,090
(Kai loses again)

206
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,140
Is K-pop okay?

207
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:38,720
Yeah.

208
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:39,890
Congratulations.

209
00:09:39,890 --> 00:09:40,710
Thank you.

210
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,470
Chinese dance.

211
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,000
Thank you.

212
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:45,890
K-pop.

213
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,360
We pick K-pop.

214
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,920
K-pop.

215
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:50,850
Okay.

216
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,430
(Song selection results
Latin: Kai & Ryu)

217
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:53,170
(K-pop: Eugene & Cannon
U.Jay & Poom)

218
00:09:53,170 --> 00:09:55,440
So we'll start practicing now.

219
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,720
And this time...

220
00:09:57,740 --> 00:10:01,650
(Top dance teachers have arrived)
we have amazing dancers joining us.

221
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:12,320
(Top dancers join, bringing new energy)

222
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,260
So practice well.

223
00:10:15,470 --> 00:10:18,680
Everyone, please focus on training.

224
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,960
Good luck to you all.

225
00:10:21,530 --> 00:10:22,690
Practice hard.

226
00:10:28,470 --> 00:10:29,080
Time to eat!

227
00:10:29,085 --> 00:10:29,810
(After a tough day of practice,
a good meal heals the soul)

228
00:10:29,810 --> 00:10:30,880
Eat more today.

229
00:10:34,590 --> 00:10:36,450
It's Chinese food today.

230
00:10:36,850 --> 00:10:37,820
Chinese cuisine.

231
00:10:37,820 --> 00:10:39,130
(Wow!)

232
00:10:39,130 --> 00:10:40,570
(Happy)

233
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,560
Thank you.

234
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:43,020
Hungry?

235
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,010
A little.

236
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:44,840
He's very hungry.

237
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,890
(Joking as usual)
That's not true.

238
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:48,660
You just said
what was really on your mind.

239
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:50,510
(Really hungry)

240
00:10:50,510 --> 00:10:52,560
Okay, let's eat.

241
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:54,660
(Let's dig in)

242
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:55,980
Eat.

243
00:10:57,090 --> 00:10:57,980
(Big bite)

244
00:11:00,330 --> 00:11:01,970
(Picks up the bowl)

245
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:04,300
(Good food)

246
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:08,180
(Chewing slowly)

247
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:12,810
(Savoring the taste)

248
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:14,970
(Finish in one bite)

249
00:11:15,220 --> 00:11:16,080
Do you want the dumpling?

250
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,710
(Give it a try)
Thank you.

251
00:11:21,170 --> 00:11:21,800
Dumpling?

252
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:22,370
Yes.

253
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,020
Dumpling.

254
00:11:25,020 --> 00:11:26,460
This dumpling is so good.

255
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:28,370
(Delicious)

256
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:29,690
How was today?

257
00:11:30,010 --> 00:11:31,010
(Tell us)

258
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:32,590
Well...

259
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,480
I was very happy.

260
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,110
(Very happy)

261
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:34,570
Very happy?

262
00:11:34,570 --> 00:11:37,840
I got a good result
working with my partner.

263
00:11:38,310 --> 00:11:39,010
Not bad.

264
00:11:39,570 --> 00:11:42,200
Did you find it difficult?

265
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:43,580
The dance was really hard.

266
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:45,420
At least for me, the dance was.

267
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:50,370
You have to really feel it deeply
and truly understand it.

268
00:11:50,370 --> 00:11:51,210
Because this is a duet,

269
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:53,760
It's different from working alone
or in a big team.

270
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:56,080
Working as a duo,
especially with the language barrier

271
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:58,620
was a challenge we had to overcome.

272
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:04,450
(Things will become better)
We'll do even better in the future.

273
00:12:06,170 --> 00:12:09,500
Today is just the beginning.

274
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,550
We have friends from China

275
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:14,790
who are improving with us.

276
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:18,110
No matter what obstacles he faces,
he never stops.

277
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:22,280
We keep improving together,
and that makes me really happy.

278
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,800
I challenged myself a lot today.

279
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,720
And he also taught me many things.

280
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,480
I'm really grateful to him.

281
00:12:28,230 --> 00:12:33,600
The most important thing
on this path we're walking on

282
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,620
