552
00:25:24,630 --> 00:25:25,740
I thought

553
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,480
I remembered the very first rule was

554
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:29,010
to not leave.

555
00:25:29,150 --> 00:25:30,420
It's quite irresponsible.

556
00:25:30,420 --> 00:25:31,940
He'll affect his teammate.

557
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:34,330
I think this is
a very unacceptable thing.

558
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:37,620
I feel sorry for Leo.

559
00:25:37,620 --> 00:25:41,040
I saw Leo's expression
become much more serious.

560
00:25:42,950 --> 00:25:45,030
I hope everyone understands
this is what a partnership is like.

561
00:25:45,030 --> 00:25:46,550
If one person makes a mistake,

562
00:25:46,550 --> 00:25:48,080
the other will be impacted too.

563
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:52,080
(If one person makes a mistake,
the other is affected too)

564
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:54,840
I went out to see
if there were any suitable clothes.

565
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:55,800
Then

566
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:57,360
I met some friends

567
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,780
because they happened to be in Thailand.

568
00:25:58,780 --> 00:26:00,070
We had a small drink before coming back.

569
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:06,440
I was very discouraged.

570
00:26:07,430 --> 00:26:10,450
I was left alone in the end,

571
00:26:10,450 --> 00:26:13,490
especially after spending
a few days with him.

572
00:26:13,490 --> 00:26:15,960
I know if he's by himself,

573
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:18,420
he won't practice.

574
00:26:18,420 --> 00:26:20,790
So the hard work will fall on me.

575
00:26:20,790 --> 00:26:23,670
(All he can do is practice alone)
I have to learn and teach him later

576
00:26:23,670 --> 00:26:24,920
(All he can do is practice alone)
because we're performing tomorrow.

577
00:26:29,140 --> 00:26:31,980
Even if there's no one
across form him at the start,

578
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:35,000
his gaze should still feel like
there is someone there.

579
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:35,880
(The practice becomes more difficult)

580
00:26:36,020 --> 00:26:38,680
If you have time
to practice with Jony later,

581
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,230
you have to tell him these key points.

582
00:26:40,540 --> 00:26:41,480
Yeah, and practice more.

583
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:44,070
Because it's the last day today.
You're out of time.

584
00:26:44,180 --> 00:26:46,810
What I can do now

585
00:26:46,810 --> 00:26:49,310
(Adjusts himself and return to practice)
is to do my part well.

586
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:51,230
Four and one and two.

587
00:26:51,430 --> 00:26:51,910
Three.

588
00:26:52,190 --> 00:26:53,380
And two.

589
00:26:53,990 --> 00:26:54,680
Two.

590
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:56,510
One.

591
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:05,510
We picked a Chinese dance this time.

592
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:08,120
I might just be a little better at it.

593
00:27:08,680 --> 00:27:11,340
Everything went well.

594
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:13,030
He's better at dancing

595
00:27:13,030 --> 00:27:14,050
and expressing himself,

596
00:27:14,170 --> 00:27:15,140
so he taught me too.

597
00:27:15,990 --> 00:27:18,100
I try my best to lead everyone

598
00:27:18,100 --> 00:27:19,730
to become more familiar with the dance.

599
00:27:20,030 --> 00:27:22,160
I hope everyone can do even better.

600
00:27:23,430 --> 00:27:25,680
Okay. Let's run it once without music.

601
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:26,800
Okay.

602
00:27:27,130 --> 00:27:29,790
I'm really grateful
to my partner, Cannon.

603
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:34,040
He's very proactive
in teaching me the steps

604
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:35,130
over and over again.

605
00:27:35,330 --> 00:27:36,890
We practiced it many times.

606
00:27:36,890 --> 00:27:38,190
Did I do well?

607
00:27:38,330 --> 00:27:39,510
- Yes.
- Yes.

608
00:27:43,790 --> 00:27:47,320
Three, four, and one,
and two, and three.

609
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:58,300
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, right.

610
00:27:58,300 --> 00:27:59,840
Five, six, seven, eight.

611
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:02,970
Yes.

612
00:28:03,340 --> 00:28:07,690
(What will tomorrow's
dance assessment be like?)

613
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,060
(Day of the assessment)

614
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:10,810
Hello.

615
00:28:11,040 --> 00:28:12,050
Hi.

616
00:28:12,530 --> 00:28:15,160
After two days of dance practice,

617
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:18,140
how are you all feeling now?

618
00:28:18,490 --> 00:28:19,270
Very nervous.

619
00:28:19,470 --> 00:28:20,220
Very nervous?

620
00:28:20,220 --> 00:28:20,680
Yes.

621
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:21,440
(Nervous +1)
Nervous.

622
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:21,980
Nervous.

623
00:28:21,980 --> 00:28:23,790
I feel very nervous.

624
00:28:23,790 --> 00:28:26,180
Even more so.

625
00:28:26,180 --> 00:28:27,090
(Cute)

626
00:28:28,510 --> 00:28:29,590
Nervous.

627
00:28:29,590 --> 00:28:35,680
(Anticipate)
But also excited for the performances.

628
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:38,170
No matter what happens,

629
00:28:38,170 --> 00:28:39,820
we've given it our all.

630
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:41,760
I believe everyone will do our best too.

631
00:28:42,060 --> 00:28:44,160
I'm so hot.

632
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,780
Very hot.

633
00:28:51,180 --> 00:28:52,290
Are you ready?

634
00:28:53,070 --> 00:28:54,520
Maybe everyone's just too enthusiastic.

635
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:56,610
(Very excited)

636
00:28:57,530 --> 00:29:00,580
I feel very nervous,
and my body hurts a little.

637
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:01,680
(Funny)

638
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:02,720
My body hurts a bit.

639
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,930
My feet and my back hurts.

640
00:29:05,650 --> 00:29:06,830
What?

641
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:07,800
Oh.

642
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:10,440
(Got it)

643
00:29:10,770 --> 00:29:12,190
(Very happy)

644
00:29:12,190 --> 00:29:12,920
Okay.

645
00:29:13,510 --> 00:29:15,570
Then let's invite the first group.

646
00:29:16,010 --> 00:29:17,130
(The first group to perform is...)

647
00:29:21,060 --> 00:29:21,720
Us!

648
00:29:22,210 --> 00:29:23,490
They're so eager.

649
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,440
The first group is...

650
00:29:27,180 --> 00:29:29,940
Pippin and Tron.

651
00:29:29,940 --> 00:29:31,570
(The first group to the stage)

652
00:29:31,570 --> 00:29:32,560
Great!

653
00:29:36,940 --> 00:29:38,080
(Come with me)
Let's go!

654
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:38,830
Let's go!

655
00:29:38,830 --> 00:29:39,240
Hello, everyone.

656
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,640
Our team is called Trpin.

657
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:43,400
(Team name: Trpin)
It mixes the first half of Tron's name

658
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:43,680
(Smile)

659
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,440
and the second half of my name.

660
00:29:45,440 --> 00:29:47,320
Trpin means something
like "over the top"

661
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:48,440
or "too crazy".

662
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:50,250
Since we both have high energy,

663
00:29:50,250 --> 00:29:51,760
(High-energy duo)
we came up with this name.

664
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:53,070
It fits our personalities well.

665
00:29:53,070 --> 00:29:55,080
It also means "to trip"

666
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:57,250
because we keep tripping over our feet.

667
00:29:57,250 --> 00:30:00,300
We tripped quite a lot at the beginning.

668
00:30:00,300 --> 00:30:00,890
Okay.

669
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:03,120
We're Paw Petrol.

670
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:03,980
(Coming up with a name on the spot)
Paw Petrol?

671
00:30:03,980 --> 00:30:04,690
Yeah.

672
00:30:05,060 --> 00:30:08,140
Because we both like dogs.

673
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:09,550
(Both very happy)

674
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:10,870
Paw Petrol.

675
00:30:11,350 --> 00:30:12,970
Are you ready?

676
00:30:12,970 --> 00:30:13,710
Yes.

677
00:30:13,710 --> 00:30:14,490
Okay.

678
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:15,980
(100% confidence)

679
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:16,810
Actually, for me,

680
00:30:16,810 --> 00:30:18,430
ranking isn't that important.

681
00:30:18,430 --> 00:30:21,970
Just completing it makes me happy.

682
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:24,600
We only had two days to practice,
which is a huge challenge.

683
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:27,350
And it's a style of dance
I've never tried before.

684
00:30:27,350 --> 00:30:28,590
So it's even more.

685
00:30:30,700 --> 00:30:32,220
(First group: Pippin and Tron
"Chinese dance")

686
00:30:41,990 --> 00:30:43,430
Oh wow, there's storytelling in it.

687
00:30:43,430 --> 00:30:44,090
Yeah.

688
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:18,590
(Encouraging each other)

689
00:32:18,590 --> 00:32:20,140
This is my first time

690
00:32:20,140 --> 00:32:22,430
working with a foreign contestant.

691
00:32:22,430 --> 00:32:25,480
And it's Tron's first time
trying this kind of dance style.

692
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,110
For the two of us,

693
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:28,260
being able to complete this performance

694
00:32:28,260 --> 00:32:29,720
already makes me very satisfied.

695
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,080
So I'm not nervous at all.

696
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:34,870
He already gave it his all.

697
00:32:35,020 --> 00:32:38,090
And I gave it everything I had too.

698
00:32:38,090 --> 00:32:40,790
As for the result,

699
00:32:40,790 --> 00:32:41,540
I think...

700
00:32:41,540 --> 00:32:44,500
Watching your first-day rehearsal,
I was a bit worried.

701
00:32:44,500 --> 00:32:47,070
Your movements

702
00:32:47,070 --> 00:32:51,110
looked a bit stiff.

703
00:32:51,110 --> 00:32:53,530
(Not flexible enough)
Stiff.

704
00:32:53,530 --> 00:32:54,780
And you seemed very nervous.

705
00:32:55,220 --> 00:32:56,410
(Nervous)

706
00:32:58,050 --> 00:33:02,150
But today, your performance
was really good.

707
00:33:02,390 --> 00:33:04,580
(Very happy)

708
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:06,570
Thank you.

709
00:33:08,490 --> 00:33:11,880
Overall, today was
better than yesterday.

710
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,110
Thank you.

711
00:33:13,490 --> 00:33:17,050
But as a team,
it still felt a bit disconnected.

712
00:33:17,050 --> 00:33:18,170
(Not enough teamwork)

713
00:33:18,580 --> 00:33:26,400
Mr. Rikimaru really
values teamwork in the scoring.

714
00:33:26,470 --> 00:33:27,840
He thinks it's very important.

715
00:33:27,930 --> 00:33:29,110
I just thought,

716
00:33:29,110 --> 00:33:30,600
as long as we weren't last,

717
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:32,710
that would be great.

718
00:33:32,710 --> 00:33:34,580
Personally, I'm quite happy.

719
00:33:34,580 --> 00:33:37,010
(The main thing is enjoying it)
Yeah, I really enjoyed it.

720
00:33:37,010 --> 00:33:38,370
Alright, we're done.

721
00:33:38,370 --> 00:33:39,930
(Completely unaware)
Time to clock out.

722
00:33:39,930 --> 00:33:40,730
We're done.

723
00:33:42,180 --> 00:33:44,530
Okay, the second group is...

724
00:33:44,740 --> 00:33:45,990
U.Jay and Poom.

725
00:33:45,990 --> 00:33:48,290
(Group 2 performing: U.Jay and Poom)

726
00:33:49,780 --> 00:33:51,130
Little buddy!

727
00:33:51,860 --> 00:33:52,930
Let's go, handsome!

728
00:33:53,180 --> 00:33:56,070
Hello everyone, we are TO YOU!

729
00:34:00,530 --> 00:34:01,270
Cool. Good luck.

730
00:34:01,270 --> 00:34:02,070
Please begin.

731
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:06,220
On the first day,
I put a lot of pressure on myself.

732
00:34:06,780 --> 00:34:09,910
I couldn't keep up with U.Jay's rhythm.

733
00:34:09,910 --> 00:34:12,330
But later I started enjoying it.

734
00:34:12,330 --> 00:34:15,160
I was happy
that I could remember the moves

735
00:34:15,160 --> 00:34:17,480
and dance together with U.Jay.

736
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:18,260
Then, the pressure disappeared.

737
00:34:18,260 --> 00:34:20,390
Because U.Jay would always help teach me

738
00:34:20,390 --> 00:34:23,380
and never complained about me.

739
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:24,080
It felt great.

740
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:24,540
Honestly,

741
00:34:24,540 --> 00:34:26,680
I think we worked well together.

742
00:34:26,680 --> 00:34:27,640
(The practice chemistry was good)

743
00:34:27,700 --> 00:34:30,660
(U.Jay and Poom: K-pop)

744
00:35:29,520 --> 00:35:31,400
I was a little nervous.

745
00:35:33,780 --> 00:35:39,280
I think the first half
was really energetic.

746
00:35:39,460 --> 00:35:41,730
I liked it a lot.

747
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:48,290
When you practiced,
your face was always...

748
00:35:48,290 --> 00:35:49,170
(Serious)

749
00:35:50,670 --> 00:35:53,300
But today you smiled.

750
00:35:53,970 --> 00:35:56,820
I like this feeling more.

751
00:35:57,050 --> 00:35:58,620
(Please smile more)

752
00:35:58,620 --> 00:36:02,820
U.Jay, your dancing has improved a lot.

753
00:36:04,770 --> 00:36:08,080
But your facial expressions
were a bit stiff today.

754
00:36:08,180 --> 00:36:09,600
(Not expressive enough)
It'd be better if you relaxed more.

755
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:10,350
Okay.

756
00:36:12,090 --> 00:36:13,580
When I was dancing today,

757
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:15,230
I felt like I focused too much
on being a dancer.

758
00:36:15,230 --> 00:36:18,860
So my performance
and expression were lacking a bit.

759
00:36:19,250 --> 00:36:21,060
I think that's something
I need to learn.

760
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:22,570
Mission accomplished.

761
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:26,190
But I feel a little down.

762
00:36:26,190 --> 00:36:27,070
It's like my soul left my body.

763
00:36:28,170 --> 00:36:30,260
Do you think he was upset
because I couldn't keep up?

764
00:36:31,150 --> 00:36:33,140
But he's really good.
He danced very well.

765
00:36:33,140 --> 00:36:34,470
I like his style.

766
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:41,140
The next group is...

767
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:43,020
(Nervous)

768
00:36:44,350 --> 00:36:45,790
Kai and Ryu.

769
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:49,270
(Group 3 performing)

770
00:36:49,270 --> 00:36:50,120
Fighting!

771
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:51,270
Fighting, young master!

772
00:36:51,270 --> 00:36:51,980
Fighting!

773
00:36:54,690 --> 00:36:57,350
For me, dancing is mostly
about muscle memory.

774
00:36:57,810 --> 00:37:00,120
So once I build that muscle memory,

775
00:37:00,220 --> 00:37:01,600
even if I make a mistake,

776
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:07,120
I won't react too strongly.

777
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:10,120
At first, I thought
dancing was really fun.

778
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:13,480
Yeah, because I had never danced before.

779
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:17,050
And this was my first time
having a partner to dance with.

780
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,180
So I found it interesting.

781
00:37:18,180 --> 00:37:20,510
(Group 3: Kai and Ryu
"Chinese style")

782
00:38:58,340 --> 00:38:58,970
Hello, Mr. Rikimaru.

783
00:38:58,970 --> 00:39:00,330
I'm Kai, and he's Ryu.

784
00:39:00,330 --> 00:39:03,080
(Due name: Chocolate)
Our duo name is Chocolate.

785
00:39:03,150 --> 00:39:04,030
Chocolate?

786
00:39:04,030 --> 00:39:04,410
Yes.

787
00:39:04,410 --> 00:39:05,420
(Not understood)
Chocolate?

788
00:39:05,420 --> 00:39:08,430
Yeah. One time, we went
to a convenience store,

789
00:39:08,430 --> 00:39:10,930
and we both bought a lot of chocolate.

790
00:39:12,540 --> 00:39:14,610
We realized
we both really love chocolate.

791
00:39:14,610 --> 00:39:15,890
(Chocolate brothers)

792
00:39:16,350 --> 00:39:17,050
So cute.

793
00:39:17,050 --> 00:39:17,820
Not tasty at all.

794
00:39:17,820 --> 00:39:18,670
You don't like it?

795
00:39:18,670 --> 00:39:19,170
Yes.

796
00:39:19,170 --> 00:39:19,650
(Understood)

797
00:39:19,750 --> 00:39:21,330
Can I show my accent?

798
00:39:21,330 --> 00:39:23,160
Hello everyone, we are...

799
00:39:23,650 --> 00:39:25,100
(Practicing quietly)
E and J.

800
00:39:25,100 --> 00:39:27,610
Kai, your expressions today

801
00:39:27,610 --> 00:39:28,400
and your performance

802
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:30,480
were all perfect.

803
00:39:30,480 --> 00:39:31,550
(Very happy)
Thank you.

804
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,350
Even better than yesterday.

805
00:39:38,020 --> 00:39:39,980
And your hands...

806
00:39:40,290 --> 00:39:41,520
The way you use them,

807
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,550
the final positions

808
00:39:44,550 --> 00:39:45,970
are so graceful and beautiful.

809
00:39:47,710 --> 00:39:49,380
As I watch your dance now,

810
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:52,540
you don't even seem like a beginner.

811
00:39:52,540 --> 00:39:54,910
Really, you danced so well.

812
00:39:55,870 --> 00:39:57,650
(Shy)
Thank you.

813
00:40:00,300 --> 00:40:03,230
And you didn't
have that expression today.

814
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:07,030
(Exactly the same)

815
00:40:08,730 --> 00:40:10,090
It looked very cool.

816
00:40:10,090 --> 00:40:10,770
(Very cool)

817
00:40:10,900 --> 00:40:12,210
- Very cool.
- Don't laugh.

818
00:40:12,210 --> 00:40:13,010
Okay.

819
00:40:13,380 --> 00:40:14,480
It was excellent.

820
00:40:15,510 --> 00:40:18,020
Ryu's expressions

821
00:40:19,610 --> 00:40:21,410
feel a bit traditional.

822
00:40:21,580 --> 00:40:25,730
I like seeing someone
lost in their own world.

823
00:40:25,730 --> 00:40:27,490
(Watching him lost in his dance
is captivating)

824
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:31,030
(Team E&J)
Hello everyone, we are Team E&J.

825
00:40:33,330 --> 00:40:35,700
E is Eugene.

826
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:37,710
J is Xiaojun.

827
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:44,610
I've never performed
in front of so many people.

828
00:40:44,610 --> 00:40:47,810
Only in small classes with friends.

829
00:40:47,810 --> 00:40:50,870
Never performed so seriously
in front of others.

830
00:40:50,870 --> 00:40:53,180
(Group 4: Cannon and Eugene.
"K-pop style")

831
00:40:55,750 --> 00:40:56,980
(Mic fell)

832
00:40:57,510 --> 00:40:59,010
(Concerned)

833
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:12,140
(Mic affected dance moves
the whole time)

834
00:41:12,140 --> 00:41:13,350
While dancing,

835
00:41:13,350 --> 00:41:16,060
I saw my mic fall.

836
00:41:16,210 --> 00:41:19,120
I glanced at it a little,

837
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:25,800
but I focused on dancing well

838
00:41:25,810 --> 00:41:26,740
and not...

839
00:41:26,980 --> 00:41:28,390
I'm sorry.

840
00:41:28,390 --> 00:41:28,960
(Quickly adjusting mic)
Sorry.

841
00:41:29,940 --> 00:41:31,040
So cool.

842
00:41:31,310 --> 00:41:32,510
- Super cool.
- How did you do that?

843
00:41:32,750 --> 00:41:34,450
Great.

844
00:41:36,210 --> 00:41:38,010
(Quickly adjusting state)

845
00:41:38,480 --> 00:41:38,990
Okay.

846
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:41,380
(Nervous)

847
00:41:43,700 --> 00:41:46,410
How did you feel after performing?

848
00:41:47,180 --> 00:41:48,460
A bit nervous.

849
00:41:48,460 --> 00:41:49,710
Still a little nervous.

850
00:41:49,710 --> 00:41:50,930
But I felt

851
00:41:51,590 --> 00:41:54,250
a bit better.

852
00:41:55,590 --> 00:41:56,990
I felt it too.

853
00:41:56,990 --> 00:41:59,000
I think it was fun.

854
00:41:59,000 --> 00:41:59,790
(Good experience)

855
00:41:59,790 --> 00:42:00,590
Yes.

856
00:42:00,590 --> 00:42:02,320
I also felt that being with him
was nice.

857
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:04,520
I memorize dance moves a bit slowly,

858
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:06,690
and Cannon was very patient
in teaching me.

859
00:42:06,700 --> 00:42:09,020
(Comfort from partner)

860
00:42:10,090 --> 00:42:12,860
(Warm hug)

861
00:42:14,500 --> 00:42:16,550
Every time I perform,

862
00:42:16,550 --> 00:42:18,620
my movements are big.

863
00:42:18,620 --> 00:42:21,740
(Sharing experience)
We always need to wear microphones,

864
00:42:21,740 --> 00:42:23,510
which sometimes fall off.

865
00:42:24,140 --> 00:42:25,730
But it's okay.

866
00:42:25,730 --> 00:42:28,230
Next time,
don't worry too much about it.

867
00:42:29,620 --> 00:42:32,820
I think my mic falling off

868
00:42:32,820 --> 00:42:34,670
startled me a bit,

869
00:42:34,670 --> 00:42:37,700
so I turned to look.

870
00:42:37,860 --> 00:42:41,070
(Didn't affect performance)
I couldn't help thinking about it.

871
00:42:41,070 --> 00:42:43,230
But next time, I think I will just

872
00:42:43,230 --> 00:42:46,930
(Grown)
let it happen. I won't think about it.

873
00:42:46,930 --> 00:42:48,340
(Meeting a better self)
That's pretty much it.

874
00:42:48,340 --> 00:42:49,410
Good job.

875
00:42:54,490 --> 00:42:55,500
Okay, next group is...

876
00:42:55,500 --> 00:42:56,890
Group 5 is...

877
00:42:57,170 --> 00:42:59,620
(Only two groups left)

878
00:42:59,620 --> 00:43:00,710
Tai and Deaw.

879
00:43:00,710 --> 00:43:03,980
(Group 5: Tai and Deaw)

880
00:43:05,850 --> 00:43:06,810
Deaw,

881
00:43:07,010 --> 00:43:09,130
go for it!

882
00:43:09,750 --> 00:43:12,280
(The last group to perform)

883
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:12,790
Hello,

884
00:43:12,790 --> 00:43:13,420
we're

885
00:43:13,420 --> 00:43:14,760
Paw Patrol!

886
00:43:17,270 --> 00:43:18,840
We chose this name because...

887
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:20,650
(Smiling)
we asked each other about our interests.

888
00:43:20,650 --> 00:43:21,830
I said I like puppies.

889
00:43:21,830 --> 00:43:22,740
He said he likes puppies too.

890
00:43:22,740 --> 00:43:24,760
Then I said, let's pick a fun name.

891
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:25,750
It's called "Paw Patrol".

892
00:43:25,750 --> 00:43:27,340
I thought it was "one one three".

893
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:29,060
So cute.

894
00:43:31,130 --> 00:43:32,230
Being the last performers

895
00:43:32,470 --> 00:43:34,740
is like watching everyone finish.

896
00:43:34,740 --> 00:43:37,340
Everyone performs really well
in their own style.

897
00:43:37,340 --> 00:43:38,940
I just kept thinking,

898
00:43:38,940 --> 00:43:39,720
what about me?

899
00:43:39,720 --> 00:43:40,400
What would happen to me?

900
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:42,440
What if I forget the moves?

901
00:43:42,440 --> 00:43:43,740
I wasn't that confident,

902
00:43:43,740 --> 00:43:46,110
because I was afraid that my nerves

903
00:43:46,110 --> 00:43:49,420
would make me perform
worse than during practice.

904
00:43:49,420 --> 00:43:51,180
(Pressure increases as the last group)
That was mostly what I was thinking.

905
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:53,630
It's not just seeing the other groups

906
00:43:53,630 --> 00:43:55,320
and thinking they're amazing.

907
00:43:55,700 --> 00:43:58,750
You also wonder
if you can do better than them.

908
00:43:58,950 --> 00:44:00,040
It's really stressful too.

909
00:44:19,540 --> 00:44:22,540
(Very in sync with each other)

910
00:45:39,420 --> 00:45:41,820
(Under a lot of pressure)

911
00:45:42,050 --> 00:45:43,240
I'm so tired.

912
00:45:43,240 --> 00:45:46,170
(Exhausted)
So tired.

913
00:45:50,040 --> 00:45:50,610
Follow me.

914
00:45:51,380 --> 00:45:53,390
(In perfect rhythm)

915
00:45:58,890 --> 00:46:00,340
After watching your performance,

916
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:03,440
I feel like it's not just about skill.

917
00:46:03,440 --> 00:46:06,190
(So much talent)
Expression is really important too.

918
00:46:07,340 --> 00:46:09,460
When I was watching you,

919
00:46:09,460 --> 00:46:11,000
you made me happy.

920
00:46:11,180 --> 00:46:19,500
(Mr. Rikimaru's expression)

921
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:21,530
Everyone got excited.

922
00:46:21,670 --> 00:46:23,120
(Very expressive)
Thank you, Mr. Rikimaru.

923
00:46:23,710 --> 00:46:26,130
You all have the same level.

924
00:46:26,130 --> 00:46:26,510
So

925
00:46:26,510 --> 00:46:29,200
as a team,

926
00:46:30,090 --> 00:46:30,900
it's perfect.

927
00:46:31,140 --> 00:46:32,900
(Perfect teamwork)

928
00:46:32,900 --> 00:46:34,740
I like Deaw's smile.

929
00:46:35,490 --> 00:46:36,170
Thank you.

930
00:46:36,410 --> 00:46:37,210
Thank you, Mr. Rikimaru.

931
00:46:37,940 --> 00:46:39,820
I like that feeling

932
00:46:42,060 --> 00:46:43,170
from Tai.

933
00:46:47,580 --> 00:46:48,720
After we finished performing,

934
00:46:48,720 --> 00:46:50,700
I felt pretty good about myself.

935
00:46:50,700 --> 00:46:53,030
I think it went well. Not bad.

936
00:46:53,030 --> 00:46:54,220
As for my partner,

937
00:46:54,220 --> 00:46:56,540
(Perfect score!)
I would give him ten out of ten.

938
00:46:57,050 --> 00:46:58,170
It would have to be full marks.

939
00:46:58,170 --> 00:47:01,720
You can see
that he really cares about this.

940
00:47:01,720 --> 00:47:04,020
And he put in so much effort,

941
00:47:04,260 --> 00:47:05,250
so I feel he deserves full marks.

942
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:07,700
As for today's performance,

943
00:47:07,700 --> 00:47:09,600
I'm very satisfied with myself

944
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:11,610
and our performance.

945
00:47:11,610 --> 00:47:14,860
I feel our teamwork was good.

946
00:47:16,020 --> 00:47:17,620
(The final group comes on stage.)

947
00:47:17,620 --> 00:47:20,020
Okay. Group 6 is...

948
00:47:20,370 --> 00:47:21,780
Jony and Leo.

949
00:47:21,780 --> 00:47:24,750
(Group 6 performing: Jony and Leo)

950
00:47:24,750 --> 00:47:26,010
Sexy boys.

951
00:47:26,530 --> 00:47:27,320
Hello everyone.

952
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:28,120
We are

953
00:47:28,120 --> 00:47:29,140
Loyal.

954
00:47:32,790 --> 00:47:34,910
"Loyal" means "Zhong Cheng".

955
00:47:35,370 --> 00:47:36,900
My name has "Zhong",

956
00:47:36,900 --> 00:47:37,880
and his name has "Cheng",

957
00:47:37,880 --> 00:47:39,110
so we combined them.

958
00:47:39,480 --> 00:47:41,220
That's pretty sophisticated.

959
00:47:43,200 --> 00:47:44,860
(Don't look. Inappropriate move.)

960
00:47:47,710 --> 00:47:49,780
(Confused but surprised.)

961
00:47:53,180 --> 00:47:57,230
(Nervous)
It was my first time learning this,

962
00:47:57,230 --> 00:48:00,910
so it felt pretty challenging.

963
00:48:00,910 --> 00:48:02,630
And time was very limited.

964
00:48:02,630 --> 00:48:03,810
We only had two days

965
00:48:03,810 --> 00:48:04,890
to prepare the duet.

966
00:48:05,550 --> 00:48:06,810
It was a duet dance.

967
00:48:06,810 --> 00:48:10,420
We barely had time to rehearse together,

968
00:48:10,420 --> 00:48:12,180
(Short rehearsal time with his partner)
so I was a bit worried.

969
00:48:12,180 --> 00:48:14,380
But after trying Latin,

970
00:48:15,770 --> 00:48:17,150
I found it wasn't that difficult

971
00:48:17,150 --> 00:48:19,380
(Confident boy)
since the moves flowed smoothly.

972
00:48:43,430 --> 00:48:47,390
♪When marimba rhythms start to play♪

973
00:48:47,390 --> 00:48:51,830
♪Dance with me, make me sway♪

974
00:48:51,830 --> 00:48:55,880
♪Like a lazy ocean hugs the shore♪

975
00:48:55,880 --> 00:49:00,340
♪Hold me close, sway me more♪

976
00:49:00,340 --> 00:49:04,050
♪Like a flower bending in the breeze♪

977
00:49:04,050 --> 00:49:08,820
♪Bend with me, sway with ease♪

978
00:49:08,820 --> 00:49:12,470
♪When we dance, you have a way with me♪

979
00:49:12,470 --> 00:49:17,480
♪Stay with me, sway with me♪

980
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:21,660
♪Other dancers may be on the floor♪

981
00:49:21,660 --> 00:49:25,880
♪Dear, but my eyes will see only you♪

982
00:49:34,920 --> 00:49:35,850
Ending pose.

983
00:49:38,070 --> 00:49:41,410
Leo, I feel like you performed

984
00:49:41,410 --> 00:49:42,660
the best today.

985
00:49:43,620 --> 00:49:46,560
If this were a solo performance,

986
00:49:46,560 --> 00:49:47,860
you would definitely be first.

987
00:49:47,860 --> 00:49:50,710
(Best performer)
Thank you.

988
00:49:53,540 --> 00:49:55,270
Jony, your eyes

989
00:49:55,550 --> 00:49:57,690
felt a little empty.

990
00:50:00,090 --> 00:50:01,890
He said Leo was the best solo dancer

991
00:50:01,890 --> 00:50:03,070
among everyone.

992
00:50:03,070 --> 00:50:04,540
I'm happy for him,

993
00:50:04,540 --> 00:50:06,610
but I blame myself for not dancing well.

994
00:50:06,610 --> 00:50:07,730
If not, we could have taken first.

995
00:50:08,500 --> 00:50:09,650
As a team,

996
00:50:10,540 --> 00:50:12,390
your level wasn't very balanced.

997
00:50:14,700 --> 00:50:16,300
(Mistake)

998
00:50:17,250 --> 00:50:19,290
(Moves out of sync)

999
00:50:19,670 --> 00:50:21,420
(Ahead of the beat)

1000
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:23,940
(Lack of team coordination)

1001
00:50:23,940 --> 00:50:26,430
Latin dance really

1002
00:50:27,150 --> 00:50:29,240
requires strong connection.

1003
00:50:29,240 --> 00:50:31,140
You need teamwork.

1004
00:50:31,440 --> 00:50:32,710
A much better teamwork.

1005
00:50:33,430 --> 00:50:35,580
Honestly, I performed
much worse than yesterday.

1006
00:50:35,580 --> 00:50:36,250
I'm not satisfied.

1007
00:50:36,490 --> 00:50:37,410
I already felt...

1008
00:50:37,810 --> 00:50:39,890
I already felt our ranking
would be pretty low.

1009
00:50:39,890 --> 00:50:42,250
The whole time felt a little off.

1010
00:50:42,550 --> 00:50:43,330
I didn't feel like talking.

1011
00:50:43,660 --> 00:50:46,140
During today's performance,

1012
00:50:46,970 --> 00:50:50,360
it honestly felt worse
than when we first practiced.

1013
00:50:50,890 --> 00:50:56,130
After two and a half days,

1014
00:50:56,290 --> 00:50:58,940
it feels like we barely improved

1015
00:50:59,580 --> 00:51:01,270
since learning the moves.

1016
00:51:01,620 --> 00:51:03,420
My partner really did his best.

1017
00:51:03,420 --> 00:51:07,140
(My smile is just my armor.)

1018
00:51:07,140 --> 00:51:09,660
(All six groups have finished.)

1019
00:51:09,660 --> 00:51:11,480
You all worked hard these past two days.

1020
00:51:11,480 --> 00:51:15,210
Now, shall I announce the rankings?

1021
00:51:15,210 --> 00:51:18,830
(Announcing the latest rankings)

1022
00:51:19,220 --> 00:51:20,180
First place...

1023
00:51:20,780 --> 00:51:22,860
First place comes with a reward.

1024
00:51:26,070 --> 00:51:27,500
Your reward is...

1025
00:51:30,250 --> 00:51:32,950
a full day of free outdoor filming.

1026
00:51:32,950 --> 00:51:36,620
(First place reward:
a day of outdoor filming.)

1027
00:51:36,620 --> 00:51:38,910
♪ Free like the wind ♪

1028
00:51:41,170 --> 00:51:41,750
Alright.

1029
00:51:42,360 --> 00:51:43,670
Fourth place is...

1030
00:51:43,870 --> 00:51:45,740
(Who was fourth?)

1031
00:51:50,050 --> 00:51:51,580
Pippin and Tron.

1032
00:51:51,580 --> 00:51:54,540
(The fourth place: Pippin and Tron)

1033
00:51:57,550 --> 00:51:59,500
For this evaluation,

1034
00:51:59,500 --> 00:52:00,530
I just wanted to enjoy it.

1035
00:52:00,530 --> 00:52:01,880
I didn't care too much
about the ranking.

1036
00:52:01,880 --> 00:52:03,530
As long as we're not last,

1037
00:52:03,530 --> 00:52:04,340
I'm good.

1038
00:52:04,550 --> 00:52:06,320
Honestly, the fact that we're not last
is already impressive.

1039
00:52:06,320 --> 00:52:07,780
(Great chemistry between partners.)

1040
00:52:07,780 --> 00:52:09,700
Next is third place.

1041
00:52:11,460 --> 00:52:13,900
I actually expected

1042
00:52:14,150 --> 00:52:15,910
we wouldn't make the top three.

1043
00:52:15,910 --> 00:52:18,100
(A forced smile.)

1044
00:52:19,230 --> 00:52:22,240
I thought we might end up around third,

1045
00:52:22,240 --> 00:52:24,540
so there was some pressure.

1046
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:26,980
(Nervous.)

1047
00:52:26,980 --> 00:52:28,880
I think Kai and I really did our best.

1048
00:52:30,260 --> 00:52:31,500
In my heart,

1049
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:33,780
I know I gave it my all today.

1050
00:52:34,150 --> 00:52:35,640
Third place goes to...

1051
00:52:37,230 --> 00:52:38,650
U.Jay and Poom.

1052
00:52:38,650 --> 00:52:43,890
(Third place: U.Jay and Poom)

1053
00:52:43,890 --> 00:52:45,180
Honestly,

1054
00:52:45,180 --> 00:52:47,950
I didn't expect to get third.

1055
00:52:47,950 --> 00:52:50,300
When I saw the rankings,

1056
00:52:50,710 --> 00:52:51,830
this was my reaction.

1057
00:52:57,320 --> 00:52:58,690
I'm already very happy today.

1058
00:52:58,840 --> 00:53:00,840
Being in the middle is not bad.

1059
00:53:00,840 --> 00:53:03,400
At least it's not terrible.

1060
00:53:03,400 --> 00:53:05,190
And there's still room to improve.

1061
00:53:05,190 --> 00:53:06,590
(Let's keep improving together.)

1062
00:53:06,590 --> 00:53:08,610
Okay. The second place

1063
00:53:13,510 --> 00:53:14,860
is Kai and Ryu.

1064
00:53:14,860 --> 00:53:18,790
(Second place: Kai and Ryu)

1065
00:53:22,970 --> 00:53:24,050
I'm really happy.

1066
00:53:24,500 --> 00:53:27,830
This was actually my first time dancing.

1067
00:53:28,030 --> 00:53:31,380
My first time seriously
training and performing.

1068
00:53:31,810 --> 00:53:34,500
So I'm really happy
I managed to do this well.

1069
00:53:34,500 --> 00:53:36,500
I'm quite satisfied with it.

1070
00:53:36,740 --> 00:53:39,330
Of course, it's still a bit of a pity.

1071
00:53:39,330 --> 00:53:40,690
We didn't get first place.

1072
00:53:42,210 --> 00:53:43,240
The first place is...

1073
00:53:43,850 --> 00:53:46,190
First place goes to...

1074
00:53:46,280 --> 00:53:48,950
(Who will take first place this round?)

1075
00:53:49,640 --> 00:53:51,670
I think Cannon and I
had great chemistry.

1076
00:53:52,010 --> 00:53:53,850
It felt like we were

1077
00:53:54,020 --> 00:53:55,530
on the same wavelength.

1078
00:53:56,910 --> 00:53:57,900
So we did think about it.

1079
00:53:58,220 --> 00:54:00,480
Could it be us?

1080
00:54:00,480 --> 00:54:01,350
We're not sure yet.

1081
00:54:01,350 --> 00:54:02,290
We really had no clue.

1082
00:54:02,290 --> 00:54:02,940
But since

1083
00:54:02,940 --> 00:54:07,140
we didn't make any mistakes,

1084
00:54:07,140 --> 00:54:09,340
I thought maybe we had a chance.

1085
00:54:09,340 --> 00:54:11,570
The dance felt pretty good,

1086
00:54:11,570 --> 00:54:15,340
so I figured we should
at least make the top three.

1087
00:54:15,340 --> 00:54:17,750
Top three seemed possible.

1088
00:54:17,750 --> 00:54:19,740
There was still a chance to fight

1089
00:54:19,740 --> 00:54:20,380
for first place.

1090
00:54:24,560 --> 00:54:26,840
Tai and Deaw.

1091
00:54:26,840 --> 00:54:29,790
(First place: Tai and Deaw)

1092
00:54:29,930 --> 00:54:31,660
See? I told you!

1093
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:33,950
Freedom! Freedom! Freedom!

1094
00:54:35,160 --> 00:54:36,180
We're geniuses.

1095
00:54:36,180 --> 00:54:37,180
We are.

1096
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:42,880
I think my partner and I

1097
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:44,660
really communicated through the song.

1098
00:54:44,660 --> 00:54:45,450
We weren't just dancing.

1099
00:54:45,450 --> 00:54:49,020
We tried to bring energy to the audience

1100
00:54:49,020 --> 00:54:50,800
and to each other.

1101
00:54:50,800 --> 00:54:51,730
So overall,

1102
00:54:51,730 --> 00:54:54,230
I'm very satisfied
with what we presented.

1103
00:54:54,230 --> 00:54:57,870
And this is actually our first

1104
00:54:57,870 --> 00:54:59,630
real dance performance on the show.

1105
00:54:59,890 --> 00:55:02,690
Hahaha.

1106
00:55:02,880 --> 00:55:04,200
Before today's performance,

1107
00:55:04,200 --> 00:55:06,030
I already felt like our group
could take first place.

1108
00:55:06,280 --> 00:55:07,850
We came into this assessment

1109
00:55:07,850 --> 00:55:09,360
(With a goal in mind)
with the goal of getting first.

1110
00:55:09,360 --> 00:55:10,960
During practice,

1111
00:55:10,960 --> 00:55:12,140
we put in so much time,

1112
00:55:12,140 --> 00:55:13,140
so much sweat,

1113
00:55:13,140 --> 00:55:15,290
and helped each other a lot.

1114
00:55:15,290 --> 00:55:17,140
So I really believed we could win.

1115
00:55:17,140 --> 00:55:19,220
(First place)

1116
00:55:19,220 --> 00:55:21,890
Okay. The fifth place is...

1117
00:55:24,750 --> 00:55:28,480
Honestly, if teamwork
was the main criteria,

1118
00:55:28,480 --> 00:55:31,510
I think Cannon's team did better.

1119
00:55:33,530 --> 00:55:34,740
Jony and Leo.

1120
00:55:34,740 --> 00:55:39,020
(Fifth place: Jony and Leo)

1121
00:55:39,020 --> 00:55:41,410
I was actually surprised.

1122
00:55:41,410 --> 00:55:44,180
I didn't expect us to place fifth.

1123
00:55:44,180 --> 00:55:47,240
At first, I thought we'd be last.

1124
00:55:47,240 --> 00:55:48,770
Leo and I getting fifth

1125
00:55:48,770 --> 00:55:50,680
was really because he stood out.

1126
00:55:50,820 --> 00:55:53,660
Mr. Rikimaru even said he was

1127
00:55:53,660 --> 00:55:54,430
the best solo dancer.

1128
00:55:54,430 --> 00:55:56,340
So that probably means I held him back.

1129
00:55:56,610 --> 00:55:57,490
I'm sorry, Leo.

1130
00:56:00,870 --> 00:56:03,320
(Sixth place: Eugene and Cannon
Last in this round)

1131
00:56:03,320 --> 00:56:04,970
But I want to say,

1132
00:56:04,970 --> 00:56:07,230
everyone can
have good days and bad days.

1133
00:56:07,230 --> 00:56:10,030
You might perform really well today,

1134
00:56:10,030 --> 00:56:13,140
and not be in the best shape
the next day.

1135
00:56:14,330 --> 00:56:17,580
So even though
you got first place today,

1136
00:56:17,580 --> 00:56:20,810
someone else might take it tomorrow
if they do better.

1137
00:56:21,990 --> 00:56:23,510
And it's not just dancing.

1138
00:56:23,770 --> 00:56:27,110
You also need to
keep practicing performance and singing.

1139
00:56:29,020 --> 00:56:30,940
Sometimes you also need to communicate.

1140
00:56:30,940 --> 00:56:33,340
Talking with each other
is important too.

1141
00:56:35,790 --> 00:56:38,070
Alright, you all worked hard today.

1142
00:56:38,070 --> 00:56:39,040
Thank you.

1143
00:56:39,040 --> 00:56:40,270
Thank you, Mr. Rikimaru.

1144
00:56:42,140 --> 00:56:43,550
Thank you, Mr. Rikimaru.

1145
00:56:51,140 --> 00:56:52,970
(The reward trip for this week's top CP)

1146
00:56:53,010 --> 00:56:55,060
Let the fans enjoy first.

1147
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:01,010
If you're happy,

1148
00:57:01,010 --> 00:57:01,700
I'm happy.

1149
00:57:01,700 --> 00:57:02,700
Everyone's happy.

1150
00:57:02,700 --> 00:57:03,490
Okay.

1151
00:57:03,490 --> 00:57:06,380
(Paw Patrol's happy night)

1152
00:57:06,380 --> 00:57:06,980
Hello everyone.

1153
00:57:06,980 --> 00:57:07,910
We just got off the car

1154
00:57:07,910 --> 00:57:09,030
and arrived at...

1155
00:57:09,030 --> 00:57:10,050
What's this place called again?

1156
00:57:10,050 --> 00:57:12,410
We're at Jodd Night Market.

1157
00:57:12,410 --> 00:57:14,140
Jodd Night Market.

1158
00:57:14,140 --> 00:57:19,760
We have one, two, three...
three thousand baht.

1159
00:57:20,950 --> 00:57:22,800
We're rich.

1160
00:57:22,800 --> 00:57:23,900
Yeah.

1161
00:57:25,260 --> 00:57:27,390
Alright, I'm taking Tai to eat now.

1162
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:34,410
What's that?

1163
00:57:34,410 --> 00:57:35,400
(Curious mode activated)

1164
00:57:35,400 --> 00:57:36,160
What's that?

1165
00:57:36,840 --> 00:57:38,470
(Slipped away in a moment)
What's that?

1166
00:57:38,470 --> 00:57:39,340
What's that?

1167
00:57:40,040 --> 00:57:41,500
(Why explain? Let's just try it.)

1168
00:57:41,500 --> 00:57:42,330
Let's try it.

1169
00:57:42,330 --> 00:57:43,050
Okay.

1170
00:57:43,190 --> 00:57:44,620
This one. This one.

1171
00:57:48,290 --> 00:57:49,890
This is really good.

1172
00:57:49,890 --> 00:57:51,190
(Eyes lighting up)
I want it.

1173
00:57:51,190 --> 00:57:52,530
I want some watermelon juice.

1174
00:57:52,530 --> 00:57:53,540
I love durian.

1175
00:57:53,540 --> 00:57:54,920
I also want some pineapples.

1176
00:57:54,920 --> 00:57:56,950
If you want it, go ahead.

1177
00:57:56,950 --> 00:58:01,130
Thank you.

1178
00:58:01,550 --> 00:58:02,320
There's more over there.

1179
00:58:02,320 --> 00:58:02,890
Fried chicken.

1180
00:58:04,550 --> 00:58:05,620
That one. That one.

1181
00:58:05,620 --> 00:58:06,790
Let's try it.

1182
00:58:06,790 --> 00:58:08,630
Squid shot cups.

1183
00:58:08,630 --> 00:58:10,020
(Eating raw squid)

1184
00:58:12,430 --> 00:58:13,460
It's alive.

1185
00:58:15,240 --> 00:58:16,990
(How does it taste?)

1186
00:58:20,840 --> 00:58:21,460
Is it good?

1187
00:58:33,420 --> 00:58:34,150
You have to do like this.

1188
00:58:37,970 --> 00:58:38,960
(So amazing)

1189
00:58:38,960 --> 00:58:39,910
Is it good?

1190
00:58:39,910 --> 00:58:41,510
(Gotta praise it)
It's so good.

1191
00:58:42,330 --> 00:58:44,900
That's the flavor right there.

1192
00:58:46,080 --> 00:58:47,770
Just thinking about it makes me happy.

1193
00:58:47,770 --> 00:58:50,740
Hahaha.

1194
00:58:51,560 --> 00:58:53,170
Staying up all night was worth it.

1195
00:58:53,650 --> 00:58:55,040
We stayed up all night for this.

1196
00:58:55,830 --> 00:58:57,190
That's right.

1197
00:58:57,350 --> 00:58:59,310
Let's go find the next food.

1198
00:58:59,310 --> 00:59:00,340
Crocodile meat.

1199
00:59:04,710 --> 00:59:05,790
It's good.

1200
00:59:05,790 --> 00:59:07,580
(Try this one too)
Is it good?

1201
00:59:07,580 --> 00:59:08,580
(It's good)

1202
00:59:13,000 --> 00:59:13,990
Alright, I'm done eating.

1203
00:59:15,730 --> 00:59:17,120
Let's wrap it up.

1204
00:59:17,670 --> 00:59:18,390
Okay.

1205
00:59:18,390 --> 00:59:21,070
Tai and I came
to Jodd Night Market today.

1206
00:59:21,070 --> 00:59:22,750
We bought a lot of good food.

1207
00:59:22,750 --> 00:59:26,290
We're bringing some of it back
for the others.

1208
00:59:26,290 --> 00:59:28,330
We had a really great time here

1209
00:59:28,330 --> 00:59:29,950
